article.headline: Old Dominion 86, East Tenn. St. 65
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Arnaud Dahi and Alex Loughton scored 17 points apiece, and Old Dominion shot 56 percent from the field Saturday night as the Monarchs defeated East Tennessee State 86-65. Loughton had two field goals as Old Dominion (9-1) opened the game with a 14-2 run. The Monarchs maintained a double-digit lead for the rest of the game. The final score was the largest margin. Old Dominion outrebounded the Bucs (3-6) 33-22, had 15 steals and blocked seven shots. Isaiah Hunter added 16 points and Drew Williamson 11 for the Monarchs. Tim Smith led ETSU with 18 points. James Anthony scored 15, and Chris Mitchell came off the bench to score 11 on 5-of-7 shooting.
